OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F373A1780330269
OL,3,CEngland set off from Birmingham
OL,4,CAirport for World Cup
OL,6,FEngland have departed for the World
OL,7,FCup from Birmingham Airport to their
OL,8,Fpre-tournament warm-up camp in Florida.
OL,10,FThose representing the Three Lions
OL,11,Fboarded the plane on Monday (June 1st)
OL,12,Fmorning ahead of the tournament, which
OL,13,Fkicks off on June 11th.
OL,15,FEngland's captain, Harry Kane, was
OL,16,Fseen smiling with one of the staff
OL,17,Fmembers at the airport. He'll be
OL,18,Fhoping to be the first Englishman to
OL,19,Flift the famous trophy since Bobby
OL,20,FMoore in 1966.
